Using JPA with GlassFish and PostgreSQL

https://jdbc.postgresql.org/download.html

spara postgresql-9.4.1209 filen i \glassfish-4.1.1\glassfish\domains\domain1\lib\

Restart the Glassfish server, if it is already running:

asadmin stop-domain
asadmin start-domain

Skriv i commandprompten följande

(skapa databasen i POSTGRESQL om du inte redan har gjort det)

Nu skapar vi en connection pool för databasen i GlassFish

c:/asadmin <ENTER>

asadmin> 

create-jdbc-connection-pool --datasourceclassname org.postgresql.ds.PGSimpleDataSource --restype javax.sql.XADataSource --property portNumber=5432:password=Cow$girl@!:user=admin:serverName=localhost:databaseName=pagiste pagiste_postgresql_pool

och nu skapar vi en JDBC Resource, this resource will be used in the JPA Configuration file to reference the connection pool.

create-jdbc-resource --connectionpoolid pagiste_postgresql_pool jdbc/pagiste

slutligen 

Create a JPA configuration file, and add it to the following directory in
your Maven project: src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml 

<persistence-unit name="Pagiste-JPA1-punit" transaction-type="JTA">
     <jta-data-source>jdbc/jpapagiste</jta-data-source>
     <exclude-unlisted-classes>false</exclude-unlisted-classes>
       
     <properties>
        <property name="javax.persistence.schema-generation.database.action" value="create"/>
     </properties>
</persistence-unit>
